    "faq": {
      "type": "lsc-faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What laser do you use for Laser Tattoo Removal?",
            "answer": "<p>We use Nanosure QSwitch ND YAG</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will my tattoo completely disappear?",
            "answer": "<p>Most professional tattoos require multiple sessions and can be significantly faded or fully removed.</p><p>Complete removal depends on:</p><p>• Ink depth</p><p>• Ink colour</p><p>• Tattoo age</p><p>• Skin type</p><p>Your consultation includes an honest assessment of expected clearance levels.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>Most tattoos require between 6–10 sessions, spaced 6–8 weeks apart.</p><p>Factors affecting session count include:</p><p>• Professional vs amateur ink</p><p>• Colour complexity</p><p>• Size</p><p>• Skin response</p><p>We tailor your treatment plan rather than selling fixed bundles.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Does laser tattoo removal hurt?",
            "answer": "<p>Clients describe the sensation as quick, sharp pulses  similar to an elastic band snap.</p><p>Cooling technology is used during treatment to improve comfort.</p><p>Sessions are typically short and highly controlled.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will it leave a scar?",
            "answer": "<p>When performed correctly using medical-grade lasers and proper aftercare, the risk of scarring is very low.</p><p>We follow structured protocols and assess your skin before treatment to minimise complications.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is there downtime?",
            "answer": "<p>You may experience:</p><p>• Redness</p><p>• Mild swelling</p><p>• Temporary blistering</p><p>These effects usually settle within several days.</p><p>Aftercare guidance is provided to support proper healing between sessions.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_7": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can you remove coloured tattoos?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes multiple wavelengths are used to target different ink colours.</p><p>Some colours (such as green or light blue) may require additional sessions, which is discussed during consultation.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_8": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I fade my tattoo for a cover up?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Many clients choose partial fading to prepare for new artwork.</p><p>We can tailor sessions specifically to lighten the tattoo rather than fully remove it.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_9": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is the test patch included?",
            "answer": "<p>The test patch is <strong>£30</strong>.</p><p>This is carried out during your consultation and allows us to safely assess how your skin responds to the laser before full treatment. The test patch helps reduce risk and ensures the most effective and comfortable settings are used for your skin.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_10": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What happens at my consultation?",
            "answer": "<p>Your consultation includes:</p><p>• Ink and skin assessment</p><p>• Session estimate</p><p>• Patch test</p><p>• Clear pricing</p><p>• Discussion of expected outcome</p><p>You’ll leave knowing exactly what level of fading to expect.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_11": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What payment options do you offer?",
            "answer": "<p>We offer flexible payment options to make your treatment as convenient as possible. You can choose to pay per single session or pay in full for a course of treatments for better overall value. We accept card, cash, and bank transfer in clinic.</p><p>For added flexibility, we also offer 0% finance through Klarna, allowing you to spread the cost into manageable instalments with a range of payment options available, subject to eligibility.</p><p>If you’re unsure which option is best for you, our team will be happy to guide you.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_12": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is laser tattoo removal suitable for all skin types?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Our advanced laser system is designed to safely treat a wide range of skin tones with minimal risk of pigmentation changes.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_13": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I would like to speak to someone before I book my treatment, how is best to do this?",
            "answer": "<p>If you would like to speak to someone please do one of the below.<br/><br/>- Use the enquiry button.<br/><br/>- Contact us via email at info@laserskinclinics.co.uk<br/><br/>- Call us during opening hours on 01902 256667<br/><br/>- Send us a WhatsApp by clicking the WhatsApp button on the website.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_14": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "I already had a patch test elsewhere do I need another one?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes we must conduct our own patch test before treatment can start.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_15": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What is your cancellation policy?",
            "answer": "<p>Cancellations up to 24 hours before your appointment can be rescheduled.<br/><br/>Any cancellations on the day will lose that session out of the course booking No shows will be treated the same.<br/><br/>Please note that we offer email and text appointment reminders right up until 24 hours before your appointment.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_16": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does laser tattoo removal work?",
            "answer": "<p>The laser emits concentrated light energy that targets the pigment in the tattoo ink. The ink absorbs this energy and breaks down into smaller particles, which your body’s natural processes then remove over time.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_17": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is the treatment painful?",
            "answer": "<p>Most clients describe the sensation as similar to a rubber band flicking against the skin. While it can be slightly uncomfortable, it’s very tolerable — and we can use numbing cream to make the experience as comfortable as possible.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_18": {
          "type": "faq",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How many sessions will I need?",
            "answer": "<p>The number of sessions depends on the size, colour, and age of your tattoo. Most tattoos require between 6 to 10 sessions, spaced around 6–8 weeks apart, for optimal results.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
